		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001023_0001"/><!--pb/@n='27r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Monday Morning </p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I send XXXIII - XXXV - 
<lb/>at present - 
<lb/>and some slips <add place="above">&amp; more</add> as 
<lb/>soon as my brother 
<lb/>has read them. </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I am just at them 
<lb/>incorporating the 
<lb/>corrections. I 
<lb/>think I make 
<lb/>all plain which 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001023_0002"/><!--pb/@n='27v'--> 
<lb/>as I am speaking 
<lb/>of things not 
<lb/>generally known 
<lb/>it will be found difficult for 
<lb/>another to do<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I am sorry to 
<lb/>say I cannot 
<lb/>come on the 26<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi>
<lb/>as <persName>Sir Roderick</persName>
<lb/>engaged me for 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001023_0003"/><!--pb/@n='28r'--> 
<lb/>that day a fortnight 
<lb/>ago. It is the 
<lb/>anniversary of 
<lb/>the R.G.S. 
<lb/>I send your 
<lb/>acceptance of 
<lb/><persName>Sir C. Eastlake's</persName>
<lb/>invitation<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p><persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Binney</persName> is 
<lb/>still ill. I shall 
<lb/>get him to read over 
<lb/>though not 
<lb/>correct verbally 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001023_0004"/><!--pb/@n='28v'--> 
<lb/>before publication<reg>.</reg>
<lb/><choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he Directors of 
<lb/>the Society profess 
<lb/>to be well pleased 
<lb/>with my speech. 
<lb/><choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he woodcut is 
<lb/>good I think. </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I send the woodcuts 
<lb/>too. I think I am 
<lb/>not invited to the 
<lb/>Fund dinner as I 
<lb/>declined believing I 
<lb/>should be absent 
<lb/>in <placeName>Scotland</placeName><reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="5" unit="chars"/><persName>D Livingstone</persName></p>
			
